stemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/cd5e1914-7c41-453e-9163-8aef59ff9b6d.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to compare the current sessions list against the last known state in heartbeat-state.json.\n\n**Last known state (from heartbeat-state.json):**\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7`: running\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31`: running\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e`: done (ended at ~11:27 UTC)\n\n\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258`: done (ended at ~10:49 UTC)\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492`: done (ended at ~10:55 UTC)\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134`: done (ended at ~10:42 UTC)\n- `agent:master-orchestrator:main`: done (ended at ~11:15 UTC)\n\nThe state file was last updated around 11:29 UTC with a snapshot from 11:27 UTC, so I need to check what's currently running versus what has finished.\n\nLooking at the current sessions now, I see the cron jobs are still active, but the Telegram groups and direct session have ended. There are also some older failed sub-agents scattered throughout the list, including ones spawned by the QLHV and DTLX Telegram groups, plus additional cron jobs and sub-agents that are still in various states. Looking at the session history from about 11:32 UTC, most of the state items haven't changed—they're still in the same done or failed states they were in before. The real shift is that the Telegram delivery cron and the Agent Status to Lead session have both completed and cleared from the active list, which actually brings the system back to a stable state rather than introducing new problems.\n\nI'm also noticing there's a stuck cron session from around 10:04 UTC that's still marked as running, which